[h1]Visible Production Stations[/h1]

Adds a [b]Visible Production Stations[/b] tab to the [b]Object List[/b] panel in the map. Lists all production stations currently visible on the map - both player-owned and NPC - with per-station production data and quick-navigation buttons.

[h2][b]Features[/b][/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Visible Production Stations Tab[/b]: A dedicated tab in the Object List panel lists all production stations currently visible on the map that contain production or processing modules.
[*] [b]Player and NPC stations[/b]: Both player-owned and NPC stations are included. Player stations always show the full ware breakdown; NPC stations show ware details when the Logical Station Overview visibility rules allow it.
[*] [b]Station icon with issue indicator[/b]: The station class icon is shown next to the station name and tinted in warning colour when any production module has an issue.
[*] [b]Production ware breakdown[/b]: Expand a station row to see per-ware produced, consumed, and net total amounts per hour (player stations and NPC stations where ware data is accessible).
[*] [b]Ware icons[/b]: Each ware row shows the ware icon alongside its name for quick visual identification.
[*] [b]Production issue indicators[/b]: If any production modules for a ware are waiting for resources or waiting for storage, the ware name is highlighted in warning colour and a mouseover tooltip lists the exact issue counts per state.
[*] [b]Active module count[/b]: The module count column shows how many modules are currently running out of the total installed (e.g. [b]3/5[/b]).
[*] [b]Ware grouping[/b]: Wares are grouped into [b]Products[/b] (not consumed on-site), [b]Intermediates[/b] (produced and consumed on-site), and [b]Resources[/b] (pure inputs, not produced on-site).
[*] [b]Limited info for NPC stations[/b]: When ware data is not accessible, the expand shows working/total module count and per-issue-type counts for intermediate and production stages.
[*] [b]Quick-navigation buttons[/b]: [i]Logical Station Overview[/i] and [i]Station Production Overview[/i] (when the mod is installed) icons are available on each station row.
[*] [b]Expand/collapse all[/b]: A button in the column header row expands or collapses all station rows at once.
[*] [b]Filter by issues[/b]: Option to show only stations that currently have at least one production issue.
[*] [b]Compatible with X4 8.00 and 9.00[/b].
[*] [b]Save-safe[/b]: can be added or removed at any time without affecting saved games.
[/list]
[h2][b]Limitations[/b][/h2]

Because [b]Egosoft rejected[/b] the proposal to expose a [b]C.GetMapRenderedSectors(holomap)[/b] function for retrieving the list of sectors currently rendered on the map, this mod falls back to the vanilla approach and works only with stations visible on screen.
As a result, in most cases the data covers only a [b]limited number[/b] of stations - [b]significantly fewer[/b] than the total across all currently visible sectors.

