[h2][b]Usage[/b][/h2]

Open the map and click the [b]Visible Production Stations[/b] tab in the Object List panel tab strip. The tab is visible whenever you are on any sector map view.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-VisibleProductionStations/refs/heads/main/docs/images/visible_production_stations_tab.png[/img]

All production stations currently visible on the map that contain at least one production or processing module are listed. Player stations and NPC stations are shown in separate sections.

To see per-ware production data, expand a station row with the [b]+[/b] button.

[h2]Station row[/h2]

Each station row contains:

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-VisibleProductionStations/refs/heads/main/docs/images/visible_production_station_issues.png[/img]
[list]
[*] [b]+/-[/b] expand button on the left to reveal the ware breakdown or limited-info summary.
[*] Station class icon (tinted warning colour if any production module has an issue) and the station name with sector underneath, with a tooltip showing the possible production issues.
[*] [b]Active/Total[/b] module count on the right side (highlighted in warning colour when issues are present).
[*] [b]Logical Station Overview[/b] button - opens the Logical Station Overview (tinted warning colour when the station has production issues).
[*] [b]Station Production Overview[/b] button - opens the Station Production Overview tab in the right info panel for this station. Available only when the [b]Station Production Overview[/b] mod is installed.
[/list]
[h2]Ware breakdown (player stations and accessible NPC stations)[/h2]

After expanding a station row, a table appears with one row per ware:
[list]
[*] [b]Ware[/b]: icon and name (highlighted in warning colour if there are production issues for that ware), with module count ([b]active/total[/b]) on the right.
[*] [b]Produced[/b]: amount produced per hour.
[*] [b]Consumed[/b]: amount consumed per hour.
[*] [b]Total[/b]: net amount per hour.
[/list]
Wares are grouped into [b]Products[/b], [b]Intermediates[/b], and [b]Resources[/b].

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-VisibleProductionStations/refs/heads/main/docs/images/visible_production_overview.png[/img]

[h2]Limited info (NPC stations where ware data is not visible)[/h2]

When ware data is not accessible for an NPC station, the expand shows:
[list]
[*] Working/total module count.
[*] Per-issue-type rows for intermediate and production stages (modules waiting for resources, modules waiting for storage).
[/list]
[h2]Column headers and expand/collapse all[/h2]

The [b]+/-[/b] button in the column header row expands or collapses all station rows simultaneously.

[h2]Extension options[/h2]

[b]Options Menu > Extension options > Visible Production Stations[/b]:
[list]
[*] [b]Show only stations with issues[/b]: When checked, only stations that have at least one production module in an error state are listed.
[*] [b]Data Refresh Interval[/b] (1-10, default 3): Number of UI ticks between data recalculations. Lower values make the display more responsive; higher values reduce CPU usage.
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-VisibleProductionStations/refs/heads/main/docs/images/options.png[/img]

